, DEMONSTRATIVE PRONOUNS.

21. Demonstrative Pronouns are used to point out or distinguish some person or thing.

They are either substantival-used instead of a noun —or adjectival —used with a noun.

The most common are, is, laic, ille, idem, ipse. ’
